This paper deals with computational argumentation and natural language processing, which are both subfields of computer science. The use of sequence labeling and integer linear programming for detecting argumentation structures suggests that this paper could belong to the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with the identification and analysis of persuasive essays.
